    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CHINA INTERNET MERGER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>China's Sohu.com Inc reaches preliminary agreement to acquire rival ChinaRen.com in what would be first major merger in expected consolidation of China's fledgling Internet industry (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>China's Nasdaq-listed Sohu.com Inc. has reached a preliminary agreement to acquire rival ChinaRen.com, in what would be the first major merger in an expected consolidation of China's fledgling Internet industry. Neither company is making money and Sohu.com's share price plunged shortly after it sold stock to the public for $13 a share in July. The company's stock now trades at about half that price.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith</p>
      </block>
